Class InternshipOpportunity

java.lang.Object
entities.InternshipOpportunity
public class InternshipOpportunity extends Object
Represents an internship opportunity offered by a company in the NTU Internship System.

Each opportunity contains detailed information such as:

  • Title and description
  • Internship level (Basic/Intermediate/Advanced)
  • Preferred major
  • Application opening and closing dates
  • Company details (name, department, company representative)
  • Number of available slots
  • Approval status (Pending, Approved, Rejected, Filled)
  • Visibility (shown/hidden from students)
  • Applications submitted for this internship

This class acts as the foundation for all internship-related operations, including:

  • Filtering opportunities
  • Student applications
  • Company representative management
  • Career Staff review and approval

      Constructs a new InternshipOpportunity with all required fields.
      Parameters:
      internshipTitle - the title of the internship role
      description - a detailed description of the role
      internshipLevel - the level of the internship
      preferredMajor - the preferred major of applicants
      applicationOpeningDate - the date applications open (YYYY-MM-DD)
      applicationClosingDate - the date applications close (YYYY-MM-DD)
      companyName - the name of the offering company
      department - the department offering the internship
      companyRep - the user ID of the representative in charge
      noOfSlots - number of internship slots available
      status - the approval status of the opportunity
      visible - whether the opportunity is visible to students
      applicationList - the list of student applications
